Coregonus
"Sommerbrienzlig", "BRI2": Douglas et al. 1999; 
Douglas and Brunner 2002

Brienzlig, Brienzling; often the time of the year the fish is caught on the spawning grounds is added to the name and shows that this species has a very wide spawning season: Sommer-Brienzlig (for summer) or Winter-Brienzlig (for win 
ter
). This species was historically known by local fishermen and fisherwomen as white whitefish (German: "Weissfelchen", but also Albele and Albuli). The common name for this species today is Brienzling which has an ending that is known as a diminutive suffix.
